CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 20, 1957, pg. 9 reads: " "Board Of Directors" - During Turn-About Day at McKeesport High School, these students became the "board of directors" for the day. Left to right, front row: Toma Miller and Rachel Goar.  Second row: Donna Smith, Sue Scott and Ron Pazur.  Third row: Gordon Cook, Janis Benedict and John Allen.  Fourth row: Lanny Van Eman. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of McKeesport High School students, from left, first row: Toma Miller and Rachel Goar; second row: Donna Smith, Sue Scott, and Ron Pazur; third row: Gordon Cook, Janis Benedict, and John Allen; fourth row: Lanny Van Eman
